1
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,416
[TREYNI]
Greetings, ruler of monsters,

2
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,125
and all of those
who are loyal to him.

3
00:00:23,208 --> 00:00:25,375
Please pardon
my unannounced visit.

4
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:27,875
I am a dryad
from the Forest of Jura,

5
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,666
please call me Treyni.

6
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:31,375
It is a pleasure to meet you.

7
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:33,833
Rimuru Tempest,

8
00:00:33,916 --> 00:00:38,125
as the ruler of monsters,
please help us.

9
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:40,458
We need you to defeat
the Orc Lord.

10
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,333
♪

11
00:02:20,916 --> 00:02:23,125
Uh, defeat the Orc Lord?

12
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:26,500
Come on now. Are you serious?

13
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:27,500
Uh-huh.

14
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:29,250
That's right.

15
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:30,625
[BENIMARU]
That's quite the request.

16
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:33,333
Seeing as you dropped in
out of nowhere,

17
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:35,583
you won't mind answering
a few questions.

18
00:02:36,666 --> 00:02:38,708
Why did you come to us?

19
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:41,083
There are stronger races
than the hobgoblins.

20
00:02:42,708 --> 00:02:44,208
Yes, I suppose.

21
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:47,125
And had the ogres' village
not been destroyed,

22
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:48,666
I might have gone there.

23
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,958
[ALL gasp]

24
00:02:50,041 --> 00:02:52,916
Though, even if
that were not the case,

25
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,625
I can no longer ignore a certain
individual's existence.

26
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:01,791
If our settlement were to come
under attack from the orcs,

27
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:04,500
we couldn't possibly
fend them off alone.

28
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:06,416
That's why I came here.

29
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:09,375
To request assistance
from someone strong.

30
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:11,833
You're mean the Orc Lord
really exists?

31
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:15,458
Until now, it was only a theory
we'd come up with.

32
00:03:15,541 --> 00:03:17,083
[TREYNI] Well, the dryads
have knowledge

33
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:20,125
of essentially everything
that happens in this forest.

34
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:22,750
Believe me, he is real.

35
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:24,958
[ALL gasp]

36
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:25,875
Hmm?

37
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:29,416
If she acknowledges it...

38
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,583
That means it's all true.

39
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:36,833
Hmm.

40
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:40,000
Give me some time to answer.

41
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,000
Backing the Kijin is one thing,

42
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:44,708
but taking on an Orc Lord
is different story.

43
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:47,666
I need a little more
information before I decide.

44
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:50,541
After all,
I am the one in charge.

45
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:52,416
[gasps]

46
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,541
Hmm.

47
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:58,125
Hmm.

48
00:03:58,208 --> 00:03:59,666
[groaning softly]

49
00:04:02,708 --> 00:04:04,208
[RIMURU]
Okay, back to business.

50
00:04:04,291 --> 00:04:06,875
So, let's talk about
the orcs a bit.

51
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:08,833
Does anyone know
what they could be after?

52
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:14,375
[SHUNA] Actually, I think
I might have an idea about that.

53
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:15,833
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

54
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:18,833
Uh, Souei,
about our old village,

55
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:21,000
did you investigate it?

56
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,666
Yes.

57
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:25,875
And judging by your tone,
it's bad.

58
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:27,708
You didn't find anything?

59
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:28,791
-[SOUEI] Correct.
-Huh?

60
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,166
There was nothing there.

61
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:31,666
Not one of theirs.

62
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,375
And none of ours.

63
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,041
Wait, no what?

64
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:37,541
Corpses.

65
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,000
[gasps]

66
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:41,250
We wondered how they were
getting supplies

67
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,625
for such a large army.

68
00:04:42,708 --> 00:04:46,125
How they could feed
200,000 orcs.

69
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:48,416
Are you saying
they ate the dead?

70
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:52,458
It's a Unique Skill.
Called "Starved."

71
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:55,333
[RIMURU]
What's it do?

72
00:04:57,916 --> 00:05:00,750
[TREYNI] Every Orc Lord
is born with this skill.

73
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:04,666
With the purpose of bringing
calamity and ruin to the world.

74
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:08,208
Its influence reaches all those
who serve under the Orc Lord.

75
00:05:08,291 --> 00:05:11,291
Making them devour
everything in sight.

76
00:05:11,375 --> 00:05:12,958
Doing so allows them to absorb

77
00:05:13,041 --> 00:05:15,333
their victim's strength
and abilities.

78
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:17,625
Making those powers their own.

79
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:21,458
[ORCS] The strength of
this comrade we eat is now ours.

80
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:24,958
The abilities of this prey
are now ours.

81
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:30,291
[TREYNI] It's rather similar
to your Predator skill.

82
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:37,125
In return for the Starved skill,
they have an insatiable hunger.

83
00:05:37,208 --> 00:05:40,916
The orcs march onward
with one goal in mind.

84
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,500
To sate an endless hunger
and gain power.

85
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:47,666
That is their king's, and their
whole clan's only wish.

86
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,125
[RIMURU sighs]

87
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:54,791
[RIMURU] So basically,
the orcs' goal isn't to wipe out

88
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:58,250
the superior forest races
like the lizardmen or the ogres.

89
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:01,375
What they want is to
steal their power. Right?

90
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:05,500
[RIMURU grunting]

91
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:09,166
Well, if that's really true,

92
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,500
sounds like we might need
to start worrying.

93
00:06:11,583 --> 00:06:15,000
We have the Tempest Wolves,
Kijin and hobgoblins.

94
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,041
With those powers,
we might as well set the table

95
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,833
and invite the orcs
over for dinner.

96
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:21,666
I'm sure we'd make
a good side dish,

97
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,666
but aren't you forgetting
about the main course?

98
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,291
Huh?

99
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:27,583
[BENIMARU] We have the world's
strongest Slime, remember?

100
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:29,291
Oh, we do? [scoffs]

101
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:30,541
[chuckles]

102
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,375
[RIGURD]
Hmm!

103
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:33,666
What?

104
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,000
In addition,
we were recently able

105
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:39,625
to confirm that there is a majin

106
00:06:39,708 --> 00:06:42,333
behind the Orc Lord's
sudden appearance.

107
00:06:42,416 --> 00:06:45,750
I believe this is someone
you would not wish to overlook.

108
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:48,958
A majin.

109
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:52,208
This person is
a subordinate of a Demon Lord.

110
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:53,416
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

111
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:58,041
[RIMURU] Treyni said
the dryads have knowledge

112
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,458
of everything that happens
in the forest.

113
00:07:00,541 --> 00:07:02,000
She's very shrewd.

114
00:07:03,708 --> 00:07:04,666
[sighs]

115
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,375
Rimuru Tempest.

116
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:16,333
Once again, I request
you defeat the Orc Lord.

117
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:19,416
As someone who has
the protection of Veldora,

118
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,250
has recruited the direwolves,

119
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:23,916
and became the patron
of the esteemed Kijin.

120
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,500
Taking down the Orc Lord
should be easy for you.

121
00:07:28,041 --> 00:07:29,166
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

122
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:31,041
What's your two cents,
Great Sage?

123
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,500
Can I trust the tree babe?

124
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,625
[GREAT SAGE]
The dryads are the caretakers

125
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:36,375
of the Great Forest of Jura.

126
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:37,583
They are said to be the ones

127
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:39,583
who pass divine justice
on villains

128
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:41,833
and any who would dare
to harm the forest.

129
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:42,958
[splat]

130
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,708
[RIMURU]
Sounds hardcore.

131
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:48,416
But 200,000 orcs is a lot.

132
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,041
Of course!

133
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:53,041
Lord Rimuru is quite capable
of vanquishing the Orc Lord.

134
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:55,750
I see.
Then you accept my request?

135
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,083
Yep.

136
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:59,250
[RIMURU] Shion! Don't I get
a say in this?

137
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:02,541
[SHION gasps]

138
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:08,250
[RIMURU] All right. I'll find
a way to defeat the Orc Lord.

139
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:10,125
But I'm gonna need
everyone here.

140
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:13,416
Sure. Count us in.
We'll help.

141
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,125
Yes, this is what
we've been waiting for.

142
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:18,541
We have complete faith
in your abilities,

143
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:19,875
just tell us what to do.

144
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,625
He's right, my lord.

145
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:24,125
Let's show those orcs
just how strong we are!

146
00:08:24,208 --> 00:08:25,458
[ALL]
Yeah!

147
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:28,166
[TREYNI chuckles]

148
00:08:30,625 --> 00:08:32,375
[RIMURU]
Sure, I talk a big game,

149
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,000
but what if we lose?

150
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,166
♪

151
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:44,250
If we're gonna take on
an army of 200,000 orcs,

152
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:46,208
then I think we should consider
forming an alliance

153
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,041
with the lizardmen after all.

154
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:51,125
But I'm not sure I wanna
talk to that guy again.

155
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:54,250
I am Gabiru!

156
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,791
[RIMURU]
Ugh!

157
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:58,416
I'd prefer to talk to someone
a little less stupid.

158
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,333
-[SOUEI] Lord Rimuru.
-[RIMURU] Huh?

159
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,958
Would you like for me
to go and speak

160
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:05,208
to the Lizardman Chieftain
personally?

161
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,958
-[RIMURU] Wow. Is that possible?
-Yes.

162
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:12,041
[RIMURU] The dude's brimming
with a cool confidence!

163
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:13,125
[gasps]

164
00:09:13,208 --> 00:09:14,333
Uh, okay, then.

165
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:16,166
We'll join forces
with the lizardmen

166
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,583
and lay the hurt on some orcs!

167
00:09:17,666 --> 00:09:18,750
[ALL]
Right!

168
00:09:19,875 --> 00:09:21,375
[RIMURU] The battle
will probably take place

169
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:23,875
in the marshlands
where the lizardmen live.

170
00:09:23,958 --> 00:09:26,291
Having their cooperation
will be essential

171
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:28,000
if we're going to pull this off.

172
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:29,500
I'm counting on you, Souei.

173
00:09:29,583 --> 00:09:31,833
I'll leave now.

174
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:33,375
[RIMURU sighs]

175
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:35,708
[RIMURU] Hopefully their
Chieftain is less of an idiot.

176
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:37,625
The opposite of Gabiru.

177
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:42,291
[GABIRU groaning]

178
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,583
[LIZARDMAN crying]

179
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,000
Sir Gabiru!

180
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:49,583
[crying]

181
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:50,791
Oh, you're awake.

182
00:09:50,875 --> 00:09:52,208
[LIZARDMAN]
Sir Gabiru!

183
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:54,458
Where... are we?

184
00:09:54,541 --> 00:09:56,583
[LIZARDMAN crying]

185
00:09:57,625 --> 00:10:00,000
Wait. I remember.
There was a fight.

186
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:02,833
And I was beaten
by that dopey-faced kid.

187
00:10:02,916 --> 00:10:04,000
Hmm.

188
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,750
What a clever masquerade.

189
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,291
Huh? What do you mean?

190
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:09,625
[GABIRU]
It's simple, really.

191
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:12,500
The weird little hobgoblin
who beat me

192
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:15,625
is quite obviously
the true leader of that village!

193
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:16,791
♪

194
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:18,250
[ALL]
Really?

195
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,333
[LIZARDMAN 1]
That kid?

196
00:10:19,416 --> 00:10:20,708
[LIZARDMAN 2]
He'd have to be

197
00:10:20,791 --> 00:10:22,041
or there's no way
Sir Gabiru would have lost.

198
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:23,041
That's true.

199
00:10:23,125 --> 00:10:24,375
[LIZARDMAN 2]
It's dirty.

200
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:26,208
They lied to make Sir Gabiru
lower his guard!

201
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,833
Those cowards.

202
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,291
-[LIZARDMAN 1] How dare they?!
-[GABIRU] Calm yourselves.

203
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:32,625
Only weaklings would
resort to such tricks.

204
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:34,166
[scoffs]

205
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:36,833
You're so wise.
Way to go, Sir Gabiru.

206
00:10:36,916 --> 00:10:38,250
Truly amazing, sir.

207
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,958
That's our future Chieftain.

208
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:42,750
[LAPLACE] You're doing
a bang up job, Gabiru.

209
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:46,083
Oh, no. I'm really not
all that wonderful, guys.

210
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:47,625
Wait, who is that?!

211
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:49,458
He's been here the whole time.

212
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:52,333
[LAPLACE] You're just as
marvelous as all the rumors say.

213
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:56,500
The name's Laplace,
at your service.

214
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,000
[GABIRU]
Laplace?

215
00:10:58,083 --> 00:11:00,166
[LAPLACE] Lord Gelmud has
sent me here on his behalf

216
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:02,041
to give you a teensy warning.

217
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:04,291
Warning? From Lord Gelmud?!

218
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:06,125
Uh, who's Lord Gelmud?

219
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:07,458
Don't you remember,

220
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,625
he's the person who gave
Sir Gabiru his name.

221
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:11,833
Thank you for coming
all the way out here.

222
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:15,208
Please, tell me about
this warning you speak of.

223
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:18,125
[LAPLACE] Well, we have
quite the crazy situation

224
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:19,333
on our hands.

225
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:23,125
It seems
that this army of orcs

226
00:11:23,208 --> 00:11:25,541
is actually being led
by a big scawy monster

227
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,250
known as the Orc Lord.

228
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:29,333
[LIZARDMEN]
An actual Orc Lord?

229
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:30,500
[GABIRU grunts]

230
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:33,541
[LAPLACE]
Luckily the Lizardmen Chieftain

231
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:35,416
is very capable.

232
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:38,375
Though, he is getting up there
in his lizardy years.

233
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:43,000
I do wonder, can Daddy handle
such a massive challenge?

234
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:44,666
[GABIRU]
Hmm.

235
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:47,208
Hmm.

236
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:49,833
Originally, I had planned
on taking over as Chieftain

237
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,041
after we'd run off the orc army.

238
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:54,458
But it seems
that would be too late!

239
00:11:54,541 --> 00:11:56,125
[LAPLACE]
Probably so.

240
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:58,500
♪

241
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,208
Excuse me.

242
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:04,541
I hate to rush off so suddenly,
but this is quite urge--

243
00:12:04,625 --> 00:12:05,833
[LAPLACE] Say no more.

244
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:07,708
You're returning to
the marshlands, yes?

245
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:09,875
By all means, go.

246
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:10,958
Yes, thank you.

247
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,750
Let's get moving!

248
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:14,666
[LIZARDMEN]
Right!

249
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:16,875
♪

250
00:12:23,458 --> 00:12:26,458
[LAPLACE] I'm sure
you'll do your best, Gabiru.

251
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:32,791
[ORCS] Trample all.
Trample all. Trample all.

252
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:36,208
Trample all.
Trample all.

253
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:39,666
Trample all. Trample all.

254
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:43,250
Trample all.
Trample all.

255
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:46,750
Trample all. Trample all.

256
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,041
♪

257
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:55,375
Chieftain, what are we
going to do?

258
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:57,375
The orc army's
quickly approaching.

259
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:01,625
There's not much we can do
except wait here.

260
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:03,250
We have no means
of fighting an army

261
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,125
200,000 strong.

262
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:07,750
-Right.
-[LIZARDMAN] Chieftain!

263
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,791
Sir, we have an intruder!

264
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:12,416
He's demanding to see you.

265
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:18,416
Right. Well, allow him inside.

266
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,500
But, Chieftain, it's not safe.

267
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:23,000
So you feel it too, it seems.

268
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:24,291
It's his aura.

269
00:13:24,375 --> 00:13:25,416
I do.

270
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,333
He's no simple intruder.

271
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:28,583
He's strong.

272
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:30,583
I doubt even a hundred
of our best men

273
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:32,250
could stand against him.

274
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,625
[footsteps approaching]

275
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:39,416
♪

276
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:44,916
Forgive me.

277
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,166
We're presently
in a tough situation.

278
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,791
I can't spare much hospitality.

279
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:51,166
[SOUEI]
Don't trouble yourself.

280
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:54,625
I am only an envoy.

281
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,291
I come here today
bearing a message

282
00:13:56,375 --> 00:13:58,000
from my lord and master.

283
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:00,125
[CHIEFTAIN]
Hmm.

284
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:04,958
[CHIEFTAIN] Very well.
What's the message?

285
00:14:05,041 --> 00:14:06,500
An alliance.

286
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:09,708
My master wishes
to join forces with you.

287
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:12,583
[CHIEFTAIN]
An alliance? I see.

288
00:14:12,666 --> 00:14:14,458
Unfortunately,
I have no real knowledge

289
00:14:14,541 --> 00:14:16,416
concerning your master.

290
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:19,875
My master is known
as the Great Rimuru Tempest.

291
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:22,625
He recently received
a request from the dryads.

292
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:25,208
He has sworn that he will
defeat the orc army.

293
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:26,916
[gasps]

294
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,958
A request from
the Dryads? Truly?

295
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:32,166
She informed us
that this orc army

296
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,083
is being led by an Orc Lord.

297
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:35,375
Impossible!

298
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,625
[SOUEI] You may want to
keep that in mind

299
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:39,500
as you consider
our proposal.

300
00:14:39,583 --> 00:14:41,375
[CHIEFTAIN grunting softly]

301
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:44,583
Yeah, right. Rimuru?

302
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:46,291
I've never heard of him.

303
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:47,833
This is all a ruse.

304
00:14:47,916 --> 00:14:49,041
He probably sent you here

305
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:51,083
because he's afraid
of the Orc Lord.

306
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:53,708
He should admit his weakness
and just ask for our help.

307
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:55,458
-[CHIEFTAIN] Enough.
-Huh?

308
00:14:55,541 --> 00:14:57,000
You need to hold your tongue.

309
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,500
But, sir, I cannot.

310
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,500
He's clearly here
to belittle our clan.

311
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:01,666
[groans]

312
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:02,916
[choking]
What is this?

313
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,833
[groaning]

314
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:07,583
Please, hold.

315
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:09,666
I apologize
for this one's rudeness.

316
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:14,250
And I ask that you forgive him.

317
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:17,458
I believe that your offer
would benefit us both equally.

318
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,708
[groaning]

319
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,458
[gasps]

320
00:15:21,541 --> 00:15:22,750
[SOUEI]
Pardon me.

321
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,541
I did not come here
to make trouble.

322
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:27,000
But I won't let
my master be insulted.

323
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:29,833
[CHIEFTAIN]
Strong words.

324
00:15:29,916 --> 00:15:32,875
Had I not stopped him, he would
have easily taken his head.

325
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:37,291
Judging by your aura,
you appear to be an ogre.

326
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:38,791
Are you from
the southwest region?

327
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:40,375
Was an ogre.

328
00:15:40,458 --> 00:15:42,500
My master granted me
the name of "Souei"

329
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:44,291
and then I evolved into a Kijin.

330
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,958
What?

331
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:49,291
But isn't that the superior race
born only rarely from ogres?

332
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:51,041
[CHIEFTAIN]
If that's true,

333
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:53,875
it would mean that
your master is very powerful.

334
00:15:53,958 --> 00:15:56,958
He must be of a race even more
superior than the Kijin.

335
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,541
An offer to enter an alliance.

336
00:16:01,625 --> 00:16:04,291
And what's more, it comes right
on the heels of an Orc Lord

337
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,250
appearing in this world.

338
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,916
I would be foolish to refuse.

339
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,125
However...

340
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:15,958
Concerning this alliance,
I'll accept it on one condition.

341
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:17,125
[SOUEI]
Which is?

342
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:18,916
I wish to meet your master.

343
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,041
It was Rimuru Tempest, yes?

344
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:23,916
[SOUEI]
Very well.

345
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,875
Then we shall begin
preparations immediately.

346
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:28,958
We will meet you here
in seven days' time.

347
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:32,333
You can have an audience
with my master once he arrives.

348
00:16:32,416 --> 00:16:34,041
[CHIEFTAIN]
Hmm.

349
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:36,416
You must ensure none of your men
engage in battle with the orcs

350
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,333
before we can get here.

351
00:16:38,416 --> 00:16:40,250
[CHIEFTAIN]
I understand.

352
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,250
Thank you.

353
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,083
♪

354
00:16:48,458 --> 00:16:49,708
[CHIEFTAIN'S DAUGHTER]
Chieftain.

355
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:51,791
[CHIEFTAIN sighs]

356
00:16:51,875 --> 00:16:53,416
Don't worry.

357
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,583
For there is light
at the end of this tunnel.

358
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,583
Gather everyone at once.

359
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:02,166
♪

360
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:04,291
Pay attention,
the orc army invasion

361
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,000
has already drawn
near to our lands

362
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,708
and this underground cave.

363
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:10,500
Stay calm.
We have nothing to fear.

364
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:13,083
In just seven days,
powerful reinforcements

365
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:14,458
will join us here.

366
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:17,083
Until then, we must
proceed with caution.

367
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:19,666
We need to conserve
our strength for this fight.

368
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:24,250
Under no circumstances are we
to make the first strike.

369
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:26,583
Those who fall in battle
will only be devoured

370
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:29,541
by the enemy
and enhance their strength.

371
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:31,291
Understood?

372
00:17:31,375 --> 00:17:34,000
This is what it means to stand
against the legendary Orc Lord.

373
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:37,250
And once our reinforcements
join us,

374
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,125
we'll launch a counterattack.

375
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:41,541
You must resist
fighting until then.

376
00:17:41,625 --> 00:17:44,333
I won't tolerate a single death
among my men.

377
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:47,791
[LIZARDMEN cheering]

378
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:49,416
[swords slashing]

379
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,375
[LIZARDMAN 1]
Good job. Surround him!

380
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:58,750
Was that monster
seriously an orc?

381
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:01,500
It was so strong it felt more
like we were fighting an ogre.

382
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:03,333
[LIZARDMAN 2]
It's hard to believe.

383
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:06,416
And just think,
there's 200,000 of these pigs.

384
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,791
[LIZARDMAN 1] That must be
the power of the Orc Lord.

385
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:12,666
We still have to defend
this place for three more days.

386
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:15,500
[GABIRU] If all we do is defend,
then we'll exhaust our strength.

387
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,083
[gasps]
It can't be.

388
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:24,250
-[GABIRU] Father.
-[CHIEFTAIN] Hmm?

389
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:26,291
Ah! You've returned.

390
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:29,625
Now then, tell me
all about your travels.

391
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,708
Were you able
to recruit any goblins?

392
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,250
Yes.

393
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,333
Seven thousand altogether.

394
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:36,833
I have them on standby.

395
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:38,166
Hmm.

396
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,583
But why are our forces in hiding

397
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:43,083
instead of preparing for battle?

398
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:44,708
The lizardmen are a proud race,

399
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:47,750
we should be fighting orcs,
not cowering in a cave.

400
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:50,291
Ah, while you were away
on your recruitment mission,

401
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:52,958
we were approached
with an offer of alliance.

402
00:18:53,041 --> 00:18:55,708
Until our friends arrive
with reinforcements,

403
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:58,291
our best strategy
is to focus on defense.

404
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:00,833
[sighs]

405
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:02,500
You've aged, Father.

406
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:03,791
I've what?

407
00:19:05,583 --> 00:19:06,458
[hisses]

408
00:19:06,541 --> 00:19:07,958
♪

409
00:19:08,041 --> 00:19:09,083
[gasps]

410
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:12,666
I agree utilizing
these natural labyrinths

411
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:15,250
may be a wise strategy
against a large army.

412
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:17,958
And yet, it also divides
our forces

413
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:19,833
between too many
separate corridors.

414
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:22,375
And stops us from meeting
our enemies at full strength.

415
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:26,500
Wait, Gabiru.
What's the meaning of all this?

416
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:29,041
Remain calm,
captain of the guard.

417
00:19:29,125 --> 00:19:30,791
I have no intention
of harming you.

418
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:31,708
But...

419
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,000
[GABIRU]
I promise to apologize later

420
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:37,166
for resorting to violence.

421
00:19:37,250 --> 00:19:38,916
And I hate to restrain you,

422
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,041
but bear with it until my men
and I defeat the Orc Lord.

423
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:45,250
Son, no.

424
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,125
Please, I beg you
not to do this.

425
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:48,541
[CHIEFTAIN'S DAUGHTER]
Gabiru.

426
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:49,958
Brother, please!

427
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,083
This is madness!

428
00:19:51,166 --> 00:19:52,541
[CHIEFTAIN]
Unhand me!

429
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:56,166
Let-let go at once!
You're making a mistake!

430
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,166
I won't stand for this!

431
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:01,541
Sir Gabiru, here.

432
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:04,833
That belongs to Father.

433
00:20:04,916 --> 00:20:06,375
♪

434
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:15,083
Wait, this power...

435
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:17,875
Vortex Spear.

436
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:20,541
Does this mean you acknowledge
me as your master?

437
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:26,916
Sir, we've seized the leaders
of each clan per your request.

438
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,833
As it turns out,
a lot of the younger lizardmen

439
00:20:28,916 --> 00:20:31,666
also did not agree
with these defensive tactics.

440
00:20:32,708 --> 00:20:33,791
Good work.

441
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:37,708
We'll gladly follow your orders.

442
00:20:37,791 --> 00:20:39,250
We're yours, Sir Gabiru.

443
00:20:41,166 --> 00:20:44,166
Thank you. Now, get ready.

444
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:47,375
I'll show you how a true
lizardman fights.

445
00:20:47,458 --> 00:20:48,708
The time has come!

446
00:20:48,791 --> 00:20:51,375
[LIZARDMEN cheering]

447
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:54,708
[LIZARDMEN]
Gabiru! Gabiru!

448
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:55,916
Gabiru!

449
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,916
[ORCS]
Trample all. Trample all.

450
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,166
Trample all. Trample all...

451
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:06,333
[RIMURU] The orc army
soon enveloped the marshlands.

452
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:09,708
Then, from one corner
of their ranks, commotion arose.

453
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,250
[groaning]

454
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,500
[GABIRU]
There is no need to fear

455
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:16,750
these pigs any more than before.

456
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:19,208
These marshlands
are our domain!

457
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:22,666
We will throw the orcs
into confusion with our agility.

458
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:24,625
Those pigs are just big dimwits

459
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,708
whose feet will
get stuck in the mud!

460
00:21:26,791 --> 00:21:28,000
All right!

461
00:21:28,083 --> 00:21:29,208
[LIZARDMAN]
We're making a dent.

462
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:30,750
Sure are.

463
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:33,875
I told you these orcs
were no match for the lizardmen!

464
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:36,000
Right! Withdraw for now.

465
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,708
[RIMURU]
Gabiru's men had to acknowledge

466
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:40,750
his tactical talents.

467
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,333
[LIZARDMAN screaming]

468
00:21:43,458 --> 00:21:44,541
[GABIRU]
What's happening?

469
00:21:46,541 --> 00:21:49,000
[RIMURU] But there was one thing
they didn't account for.

470
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:51,083
Something Gabiru didn't know.

471
00:21:52,208 --> 00:21:54,083
The Orc Lord's terror.

472
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:57,541
The orcs are eating
other orcs?

473
00:21:57,625 --> 00:21:59,583
♪

474
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:01,375
[RIMURU]
Their Chieftain knew this.

475
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:03,416
About the Orc Lord's influence.

476
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:08,416
That gap in knowledge would have
consequences for Gabiru,

477
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,541
as he would soon see.

478
00:22:10,625 --> 00:22:12,375
[ORCS]
Trample all.

479
00:22:12,458 --> 00:22:15,583
Trample all. Trample all.

480
00:22:15,666 --> 00:22:18,958
The strength of this comrade
we eat is now ours.

481
00:22:19,041 --> 00:22:21,750
The abilities of this prey
are now ours!

482
00:23:53,166 --> 00:23:55,500
[GREAT SAGE] Next time,
"The Great Clash."

